<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-552] Lustre Wiki: Migrate Lustre Protocol Documentation to Wiki</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-552</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This improvement tracks creation of a Lustre Wiki page that captures opcodes in Lustre and provides some basic descriptions for each.&#160; This derives from an email chain where Michael Aguilar at Sandia and Andreas Dilger were discussing the now long-abandoned Lustre Protocol Documentation project, which is still present here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://git.whamcloud.com/?p=doc/protocol.git;a=summary&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git.whamcloud.com/?p=doc/protocol.git;a=summary&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Andreas mentions that:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&quot;Probably the easiest source is ll_rpc_opcode_table[] that maps all of the RPC opcode numbers to string names.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

